        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="xpu-Latn" resp="#JP" source="#autopsy">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:r-to-l"/>mnṣpt
                    <lb n="2" style="text-direction:r-to-l"/><persName type="attested"><name>ḥṭʾlm</name>
                    <lb n="3" style="text-direction:r-to-l"/><name>mms</name>
                    <lb n="4" style="text-direction:r-to-l"/>bn <name>bʿ
                    <lb n="5" style="text-direction:r-to-l"/>lytn</name></persName>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text of De Simone</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#RDS">
                <p>Stele of ḥṭʾlm mms son of bʿlytn.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#RDS">
                <p>Stele di ḥṭʾlm mms figlio di bʿlytn.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#RDS">
                <p>ḥṭʾlm: a hapax in phoenician onomastics. mms: punic personal name, unexplained. bʿlytn: phoenician personal name “Baal has given”, Latin transcription attested in various inscriptions, e.g.: BALITHONIS (CIL V 4920), BALIATON (CIL VIII 16011, 27491), BALIATHO (CIL VIII 68, AE 1992 1781).</p>
            </div>
